        <h1>Nils Matteson</h1>
        <p>I build systems for LLM inference: GPU and CUDA, distributed systems, applied ML. I like problems where the deliverable is a number someone else can re-run.</p>
        <p>The thing I keep pulling on: a transformer mid-generation is a multi-gigabyte data structure that the entire ecosystem treats as disposable. Treating it as a first-class artifact instead got me thaw (below), an open PR against vLLM core, and a sole-author research preprint measuring what the standard replay shortcut actually does to token-level credit estimates (also below).</p>
        <p>B.S. Data Science, CS minor, UW-Madison, May 2026. M.S. CS, Northeastern Silicon Valley, San Jose, starting September 2026. The longer plan is research: measurement problems in ML systems, then a PhD.</p>
        <p>Open to SWE/MLE internship Summer 2027, full-time 2028. GPU inference, distributed systems, ML infrastructure.</p>
        <p>
          mail <a href="mailto:nils@thaw.sh">nils@thaw.sh</a> &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;
          code <a href="https://github.com/matteso1">github.com/matteso1</a> &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;
          <a href="/resume.pdf">resume.pdf</a>
        </p>
